How should you allocate your portfolio to meet a target return of 10% with minimum risk?
A) 50% A, 50% B
B) 25% A, 25% B, 50% C
C) 33% A, 33% B, 33% C
D) It doesn’t matter because all 3 stocks have the same risk.
