b) The portion of the company's annual earnings going to dividends will increase.
c) The number of dividend payouts will increase per year.
d) The number of dividend payouts will decrease per year.
Correct answer is b) because the payout ratio indicates the proportion of money returned to stockholders from a company's annual earnings.
