Chapter 8
Given a market for which the semi-strong version of the EMH is valid, which of the following types of information (if any) can be exploited by investors in order to outperform the market?
        1) Technical
        2) Fundamental
        3) Insider
a) 1, 2, 3
b) 2, 3
c) 3
d) None of These
Correct answer:  C
Rationale:  In the semi-strong form of the EMH prices adjust rapidly to new public information.  This includes historical price data, quarterly reports, and any other publicly available information.  Therefore, analysis of technical and fundamental data cannot be used to outperform the market.  However, the semi-strong form of the EMH does allow for insider information, thus it can be used to outperform the market.
